Raw Text:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 58
H.P. 22 House of Representatives, January 8, 2025
An Act to Establish Certain Positions Within the Maine Bureau of
Veterans' Services
Submitted by the Department of Defense, Veterans and Emergency Management pursuant
to Joint Rule 204.
Received by the Clerk of the House on January 6, 2025. Referred to the Committee on
Veterans and Legal Affairs pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed pursuant to Joint
Rule 401.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative SUPICA of Bangor.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 37-B MRSA §503, sub-§1, as amended by PL 2009, c. 406, §8, is further
3 amended to read:
4 1. Employment of personnel. The director may employ, subject to approval of the
5 appointing authority and the Civil Service Law, the personnel necessary to administer this
6 chapter. The director may employ a deputy director, a superintendent of the cemetery
7 system, a veteran claims specialist and veteran service officers a deputy superintendent of
8 the cemetery system, a supervisor of veterans' services, a deputy supervisor of veterans'
9 services and veterans' services officers. The director and other employees referred to in
10 this subsection must be veterans as defined by 38 United States Code, Section 101 (2)
11 101(2) who were separated with an honorable discharge.
12 SUMMARY
1133 This bill changes the titles of positions that must be filled by veterans that may be
1144 employed by the Director of the Maine Bureau of Veterans' Services within the Department
1155 of Defense, Veterans and Emergency Management to more closely align with current
1166 human resources job descriptions. It also adds several positions to the list of positions in
1177 the Maine Bureau of Veterans' Services that must be filled by veterans and corrects a
1188 cross-reference.
